Evidence based and emerging dietary approaches to upper Disorders of Gut-Brain Interaction.
Emerging data based on 6-food elimination diet and confocal laser endomicroscopic evaluation of mucosal responses to food proteins, suggest a role for duodenal allergic reactions in FD symptom generation. In gastroparesis, a low residue diet has been shown to improve symptoms. Novel dietary approaches under evaluation are the Mediterranean diet and the heating/cooling diet approach.
